race.comment: Tough way to finish the card. NICISH (9) just keeps fronting up and hasn't run a poor race all campaign. If she's not winning, she's going down narrowly and that is probably the knock. But she's drawn perfectly here to settle a tad closer and will be in the finish. She can win. SWIFTIE HARRIET (12) might be ready third-up. She's appeared to have every chance in both runs this campaign but just lacked the killer punch at the end of her races. Holder goes on but she's drawn wide, which may see her concede a start. HYPERNOVA (5) finished just behind both NICISH and SWIFTIE HARRIET last start. He's drawn well to potentially settle closer and can win if things go his way. GINGER SINNER (8) looks well-placed up to 1200m and can run in the money, while VALLENCOURT (15) can go forward with the claim and take some catching.
